se></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533736\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533736\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xht1665702703856.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xht1665702703856.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xht1665702703856.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xht1665702703856\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                       \n Database Integrity Support\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"xht1665702703856__database_integrity_support_143736\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Database integrity support includes referential integrity checking, locking, and transaction control, including two-phase commit. The type and degree of support for these features varies with the database.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xht1665702703856__p_d47465e1_d47466e1_d47467e1\">By default, Uniface handles referential integrity checking. For some databases, it is possible for the database itself to handle referential integrity, in which case a connector option disables or enables Uniface referential integrity. The name of this option is DBMS-specific and the default state depends on the DBMS connector used.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xht1665702703856__p_d47468e1_d47469e1_d47470e1\">Uniface locking is supported for most databases, but some restrictions or special considerations may apply. DBMSs vary in their locking behavior (optimistic locking might be the DBMS default, or different locking strategies are applied in different circumstances).</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xht1665702703856__p_d47471e1_d47472e1_d47473e1\">Uniface transactions can be explicitly defined with the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span> ProcScript commands, which are supported by most databases. Support for two-phase commit varies and other transaction control issues may apply.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xht1665702703856__p_d47474e1_d47475e1_d47476e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fnf1665702703926.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fnf1665702703926.html\" title=\"Referential integrity is a standard feature of relational database design that prevents users or applications from entering inconsistent data. Most relational databases have referential integrity rules that you can apply when you create a relationship between tables.\">Referential Integrity</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qvp1665702561079.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qvp1665702561079.html\" title=\"Locking means protecting one or more rows from being overwritten by other users while you are working with those rows. Working with rows can be defined as either the simple act of reading those rows from the database, or the act of modifying those rows after retrieving them and before storing, or the act of storing those modified rows. The state that initiates locking depends on the type of locking which has been applied or defined.\">Locking Strategies</a>, and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lnt1665702561005.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lnt1665702561005.html\" title=\"A transaction is a complete, logical unit of work. It usually involves adding, deleting or updating one or more logically related records in one or more databases. With Uniface, you can explicitly define a transaction with the commit ProcScript instruction. If an error occurs, a transaction can be rolled back with the rollback ProcScript instruction.\">Transaction Control</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"6\" id=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Database Integrity Support</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Connector</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">DBMS Referential Integrity?</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Locking?</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__4\">\n<p class=\"p\">Commit/Rollback?</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__5\">\n<p class=\"p\">Two-Phase Commit?</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__6\">\n<p class=\"p\">Details</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">DB2</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__4\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__5\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__6\">\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kdl1665702704207.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kdl1665702704207.html\" title=\"DB2 allows referential integrity constraints to be defined only on the primary key of a parent table (the one entity). Uniface allows relationships to be defined on both primary and candidate keys. DB2 does not support referential integrity on candidate keys, so Uniface must maintain the constraints if your application has any relationships defined on candidate keys.\">Referential Integrity Management for DB2</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"iio1665702704280.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iio1665702704280.html\" title=\"Full Uniface locking support (optimistic, cautious, and paranoid) is available.\">Locking Support on DB2</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qdh1665702704349.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qdh1665702704349.html\" title=\"Both the commit and rollback instructions are supported by the DB2 connector. However, you should never use them in an SQL string with the sql instruction.\">Commit/Rollback Support on DB2</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Informix</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__4\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__5\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__6\">\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"laf1665702704418.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/laf1665702704418.html\" title=\"To use locking, ensure that your database enables transaction logging. If not, use U_VERSION. All locking types (optimistic, cautious, and paranoid) are supported. The default locking type is cautious; the locking granularity is set to row locking.\">Locking Support on Informix</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gbm1665702704488.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gbm1665702704488.html\" title=\"If there is no transaction logging, the commit and rollback instructions are ignored. When there is transaction logging, both of these instructions are supported by Informix.\">Transaction Control on Informix</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">MS-SQL Server</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__4\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__5\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__6\">\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ucb1665702704561.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ucb1665702704561.html\">Locking Support on Microsoft SQL Server</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vpe1665702704630.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vpe1665702704630.html\">Transaction Control on Microsoft SQL Server</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">MySQL</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__4\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__5\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__6\">\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jtc1665702704700.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jtc1665702704700.html\" title=\"Referential integrity is handled by Uniface.\">Referential Integrity Management on MySQL</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">ODBC</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__4\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__5\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__6\">\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kvw1665702705043.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kvw1665702705043.html\">Referential Integrity Management on ODBC</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Oracle</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__4\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__5\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__6\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">PostgreSQL</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__4\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__5\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xht1665702703856__table_d4454e1_d4455e1_d4456e1__entry__6\">\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bir1665702706773.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bir1665702706773.html\" title=\"The commit and rollback comma